  "prompt": "What is a good EPS figure for stock investing?",
  "response": "A \"good\" EPS (Earnings Per Share) can vary by industry, but generally:\n\n1. Positive trends:\n- Consistently increasing EPS year over year\n- EPS higher than industry average\n- EPS growth rate above inflation\n\n2. Benchmarks:\n- Most investors look for EPS above $1\n- Compare EPS to industry peers\n- Higher is typically better\n\n3. Specific ranges:\n- Small-cap stocks: $0.50 - $2\n- Mid-cap stocks: $2 - $5\n- Large-cap stocks: $5+\n\n4. Additional considerations:\n- P/E ratio context\n- Company's growth potential\n- Overall financial health\n- Market conditions\n\nRemember that EPS is just one metric, and investors should analyze multiple financial indicators before making investment decisions.\n\nConsulting a financial advisor for personalized guidance is recommended.",
